Ekiti State Governor, Mr. Ayodele Fayose,Â on Wednesday, momentarily lost consciousness after policemen allegedly fired teargas into the Government House in Ado-Ekiti, the state capital. Following the incident, Governor Fayose was reportedly rushed to the Government House Clinic, where he was given medical treatment. A combined team of policemen and operatives of the Department of State Services had earlier laid siege to the Ekiti State Government House in Ado-Ekiti. 